Project MedScan: Secure Health QR Systems
Developer Documentation & Project Overview

1. Executive Summary
MedScan is a Flask-based web application designed for emergency preparedness.
It allows users to digitize their critical medical information into a portable QR code.
In an emergency, a first responder can scan the code to instantly view life-saving data—such as 
allergies or blood type—and save it directly to their device notes without needing a specialized app.

2. Technical Architecture
The project utilizes a robust Python-based stack to ensure speed and security.

Backend Framework: Flask (Python)

Database: SQLAlchemy (SQLite for development / PostgreSQL for production)

Authentication: Flask-Login with Werkzeug salted password hashing.

QR Logic: python-qrcode with Pillow for image processing.

Frontend: HTML5, CSS3 (Bootstrap/Tailwind), and Jinja2 templating.

3. Core Functionality (The User Journey)
A. Secure Onboarding
Users register with an encrypted profile. 
The system uses Session Management to ensure that medical forms are only accessible by the account owner.


C. QR Generation & Note Integration
When a user "Generates" their code, the Flask backend:

Retrieves the latest form data from the database.

Formats the data into a clean, readable string or vCard format.

Generates a unique QR image stored in the user's private gallery.

Feature: The QR is encoded specifically so mobile OS scanners (iOS/Android)
recognize the text and offer a "Save to Notes" or "Create Contact" shortcut.

B. The Medical Data Engine
The core of the app is a dynamic form that captures:

Vital Stats: Blood group, height, weight.

Medical Alerts: Allergies, chronic conditions, current medications.
